name: Rate Hike Refuge
description: These bonds protect against rising US interest rates via short-term loans to stable companies.
long_description: The US Federal Reserve Bank changes the Federal Funds Rate (the rate at which banks borrow from others banks) as a way to manage inflation. When the Fed raises interest rates, it costs everyone more to borrow money. Generally, this means bonds that were issued in the past lose value. Why? Well, newly issued bonds will now pay more because of higher interest rates. This fund protects against rising interest rates by investing in floating rate bonds, which automatically adjust value to track the Federal Funds Rate.

name: Long-Term Mix
description: This aggressive blend is specifically built for long-term investing—like planning for retirement.
long_description: Aggressive investing works by trading short-term stability for long-term value. This mix follows that strategy by focusing on stocks from both mature and emerging economies—while holding relatively few bonds. If you're in for the long haul, you can feel comfortable using your mix as the core of your portfolio.

name: Inflation Defense
description: Loan money to the US government while protecting against inflation with these unique bonds.
long_description: When inflation increases, cold hard cash loses value. Generally, this means that traditional bonds also lose value. Why? Well the bonds' future cash payments have also lost value. This fund protects against this by investing in TIPS (Treasury Inflation Protected Securities), which automatically adjust value to track inflation.

name: High Voltage
description: The world of utilities and power production is undergoing lightning fast change—capitalize on all of it.
long_description: Whether stocks go up or down, people always need electricity, water, and gas. Utility companies are the backbone of America, and this fund offers a practical selection that includes everything from coal to renewables.

name: Ford
description: The American industrial icon builds and sells millions of automobiles around the world.
long_description: Founded by Henry Ford in 1903 and family-operated ever since, Ford cars have been an international staple for over a century. The Detroit based company now markets vehicles under the Ford, Lincoln, and Troller marques. This is a direct investment in Ford stock.

name: AI's Top U.S. Picks
description: Built on IBM's Watson AI, this fund holds US stocks picked by artificial intelligence models.
long_description: Using IBM's Watson, this AI system mimics a team of 1,000 researchers working 24/7 to analyze millions of data points every day. The system continuously uses this data to construct predictive models for about 6,000 US companies and build a portfolio focused on long-term growth.

name: Activision Blizzard
description: The top game company in America is a legendary titan of interactive entertainment.
long_description: Spawned in a 2007 merger, Activision Blizzard runs renowned studios, Major League Gaming, and famed franchises Call of Duty, Destiny, Warcraft, StarCraft, Diablo, Hearthstone, Overwatch, and Candy Crush, among others. This is a direct investment in Activision Blizzard stock.

name: Conservative Mix
description: Looking for an all-in-one conservative option to make it easy? This diverse collection is tailored to your goals.
long_description: Your mix is a healthy blend of stocks and bonds that reflects your conservative investing profile and gives you strong diversification. You can feel comfortable only investing here. Or, you can use your mix as the core of your portfolio and supplement it with other investments that align with your beliefs.

name: BLOK
description: These companies are actively involved in the development and utilization of blockchain technologies.
long_description: The “blockchain” is a peer-to-peer shared, distributed ledger that facilitates the process of recording transactions and tracking assets in a business network. BLOK does not invest directly in blockchain technology, but invests in companies actively involved in the development and utilization of blockchain technology. BLOK is also comprised of companies that are partnering with and/or directly investing in companies that are actively engaged in this technology, as well as companies acting as members of multiple consortiums dedicated to this technology.

name: Gilead Sciences
description: Operating in over 35 countries, this biopharmaceutical company specializes in antiviral drugs.
long_description: Perhaps best-known for the flu drug Tamiflu, Gilead Sciences markets a 24 drug portfolio that contains a number of category firsts—such as complete treatment regimens for HIV and chronic hepatitis C available in once-daily pills. This is a direct investment in Gilead Sciences stock.
